								<p class="lead">Just like in Word Processing, borders and shading are formatting tools that can be used in spreadsheets to highlight or emphasize information or to makethe document more attractive and appealing. </p> 

<p>Shading and Borders can be used together or separately.</p>

<div class="row">
<div class="twelve columns">
<h4>Shading and Borders</h4>

<p> To apply shading, select the range of cells where you want to make changes and then click on the downward arrow next to the the icon that looks like a paint bucket. </p>

<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/spreadsheets/fillicon.jpg"/>

<p> To apply borders, select the range of cells where you want to make changes and then click on the downward arrow next to the the border icon. </p>

<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/spreadsheets/bordericon.jpg"/>


<p> You will find these icons on the ribbon from under the Home Tab in the Font Group in Microsoft Excel 2007/2010 or on the toolbar in Classic Microsoft Excel. </p>



<hr>
<div class="row">
<div class="twelve columns">
<h4>Shading from Microsoft Excel 2007/10 Ribbon</h4>


<p>Select the range of cells, make sure the <strong>Home Tab</strong> is selected, click on the arrow next to the icon that looks like a paint bucket, and select the color.</p>


<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/spreadsheets/ribbonshade.jpg"/>


<hr>
<div class="row">
<div class="twelve columns">
<h4>Borders from Microsoft Excel 2007/10 Ribbon</h4>

<p>Select the range of cells, make sure the <strong>Home Tab</strong> is selected, click on the arrow next to the border icon, and select the style.</p>


<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/spreadsheets/ribbonborder.jpg"/>

</div>
</div>
